{"word":"G1498 - εἴην - eíēn - i'-ane - Mean","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">εἴην</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">eíēn</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">i'-ane</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Mean</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Verb / வினைச்சொல்</span>"},{"paragraph":"வினைச்சொல் - இரு"},{"paragraph":"be, was, were"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>Optative (that is, English subjunctive) present of <a href=\"#/G1510 - εἰμί - eimí - i-mee'/1510\">G1510</a> (including the other person); <i>might</i> (<i>could</i>, <i>would</i> or <i>should</i>) <i>be:</i> - mean, + perish, should be, was, were.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}